  <help><![CDATA[
Usage
=====
This tool performs a Discriminant Analysis of Principal Components (DAPC) to identify and describe genetic clusters using the R package adegenet (Jombart et al. 2010). It is designed to work with both SNPs (VCF format) and SSRs (tabular format).

The analysis follows a two-step process:

    Clustering: Identification of groups using K-means clustering on Principal Components. The user can choose between Automatic selection (testing a range from K-min to K-max to find the "elbow" of the BIC curve) or Fixed selection to use a specific number of clusters. A Seed can be set to ensure the reproducibility of the K-means stochastic initializations.

    Discriminant Analysis: The tool optimizes the separation between the identified groups. To avoid over-fitting, the tool automatically retains a conservative number of PCA axes (K−1) for the discriminant analysis, following the recommendations of Thia (2022).

The tool generates several outputs including Summary Stats (reassignment rates), a BIC Curve (for automatic mode), PCA and DAPC scatter plots, and a Posterior Membership barplot (STRUCTURE-style) showing the assignment probability of each individual.

Examples files
==============

**SSR Genotype file (tab):**

::

    Ind     Pop     Loc1    Loc2    Loc3
    ind1    pop1    120/124 200/202 150/150
    ind2    pop1    120/120 202/204 150/152
    ind3    pop2    124/126 200/200 152/152

**Assignments table:**
+-----------+------------+------------+-----------+-----------+
| Individu  | Assignment | Posterior1 | Posterior2| LD1       |
+===========+============+============+===========+===========+
| Sample_01 | Cluster_1  | 0.998      | 0.002     | -4.52     |
+-----------+------------+------------+-----------+-----------+
| Sample_02 | Cluster_2  | 0.015      | 0.985     | 3.12      |
+-----------+------------+------------+-----------+-----------+

Note: The Assignment column corresponds to the cluster assigned by K-means. Posterior columns represent the probability of membership to each cluster.


]]></help>

